[[File:Kabul_TV_Hill_view.jpg|thumb]]
'''喀布尔'''（{{lang-ps|کابل}}，{{lang-fa|کابل}}；中國古稱'''高附'''），是[[阿富汗伊斯兰酋长国|阿富汗]]的[[首都|首都]]，[[喀布尔省|喀布尔省]]首府和阿富汗的最大城市。它是一座有3000多年历史的名城，1773年以后成为阿富汗首都。「喀布尔」在[[信德语|信德语]]中是“贸易中枢”的意思。2020年，喀布尔城市总人口达到4,222,000人。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.citymayors.com/statistics/largest-cities-mayors-1.html |title=Largest cities in the world and their mayors - 1 to 150 |publisher=City Mayors |date=2012-05-17 |accessdate=2012-08-17 |archive-date=2015-04-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150429093709/http://www.citymayors.com/statistics/largest-cities-mayors-1.html |dead-url=no }} |url=http://www.citymayors.com/statistics/urban_growth1.html|title=World's fastest growing urban areas (1) |publisher=City Mayors |date=2012-05-17 |accessdate=2012-08-17 |archive-date=2010-11-25 |archive-url= |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 歷史 ==
===古代===
喀布尔有3500年的历史，古代很多帝国都为了争夺这块战略要地而长时间地战争，因为喀布尔是连接[[中亚|中亚]]和[[南亚|南亚]]的贸易必经之路。中國史书《[[汉书|漢書]]》中記載的「[[高附都督府|高附]]」就是喀布爾{{Citation needed||time=2021-09-03}}。

===内战与塔利班时期===
[[File:Kabul_during_civil_war_of_fundamentalists_1993-2.jpg|thumb]]
1992年4月[[穆罕默德·纳吉布拉|纳吉布拉]]<ref name="Bowersox"/>政府倒台后，不同圣战者派系的领导人进入该市，并根据《白沙瓦协议》组建政府，但是[[古勒卜丁·希克马蒂亚尔|古勒卜丁·希克马蒂亚尔]]的政党拒绝签署协议，并开始炮击该市争夺权力，並很快升级为全面冲突。这标志着喀布尔黑暗时期的开始，至少有3万名平民在这个被当地人称为“喀布尔战争”的时期被杀害。 <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1996/09/28/world/guerrillas-take-afghan-capital-as-troops-flee.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2018-01-31 |archive-date=2020-10-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201010085715/https://www.nytimes.com/1996/09/28/world/guerrillas-take-afghan-capital-as-troops-flee.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 到1996年，该市约80%的地区已被破坏和摧毁，<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=Bleeding Afghanistan: Washington, Warlords, and the Propaganda of Silence|author1=Kolhatkar, S.|author2=Ingalls, J.|author3=Barsamian, D.|date=2011|publisher=Seven Stories Press|isbn=9781609800932|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=px7rU0i-71UC|accessdate=2014-10-25|archive-date=2020-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207173205/https://books.google.com/books?id=px7rU0i-71UC|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>Bowersox (p.192)</ref>老城和西部地区是重灾区之一。 [[纽约时报|纽约时报]]的一位分析师於1996年表示，和正處於[[波斯尼亚战争|波斯尼亚战争]]的[[塞拉耶佛|塞拉耶佛]]相比，喀布尔受到损害还要更加严重。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1996/02/05/world/afghan-capital-grim-as-war-follows-war.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2018-01-31 |archive-date=2020-11-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201102075843/https://www.nytimes.com/1996/02/05/world/afghan-capital-grim-as-war-follows-war.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1992年夏天，对立民兵之间的轰炸加剧，使喀布尔遭受重创。由於该市的地理位置在一个狭窄的山谷中，使其很容易成为驻扎在周围山区的民兵发射的火箭弹的目标。最初这个城市的派系联合与希克马蒂亚尔的部队相抗衡，但由于内部冲突，这个联合变迅速瓦解。<ref>Nazif M Shahrani, "War, Factionalism and the State in Afghanistan" in American Anthropologist 104:3 (Arlington, Virginia: American Anthropological Association, 2008), 719.</ref>在两年时间里，喀布尔大部分基础设施被摧毁，大量人口流向农村或国外，水电完全中断。 1994年底，民兵暫停对喀布尔的轰炸，<ref name="Afghanistan Justice Project">{{cite web|year=2005|url=http://www.afghanistanjusticeproject.org/warcrimesandcrimesagainsthumanity19782001.pdf|title=Casting Shadows: War Crimes and Crimes against Humanity: 1978–2001|publisher=Afghanistan Justice Project|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004221455/http://www.afghanistanjusticeproject.org/warcrimesandcrimesagainsthumanity19782001.pdf|archivedate=2013-10-04|accessdate=2018-01-31}}</ref><ref name="amnesty.org">Amnesty International. "DOCUMENT – AFGHANISTAN: FURTHER INFORMATION ON FEAR FOR SAFETY AND NEW CONCERN: DELIBERATE AND ARBITRARY KILLINGS: CIVILIANS IN KABUL." 16 November 1995 Accessed at: {{cite web |url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/library/asset/ASA11/015/1995/en/6d874caa-eb2a-11dd-92ac-295bdf97101f/asa110151995en.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-10-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707130613/http://www.amnesty.org/en/library/asset/ASA11/015/1995/en/6d874caa-eb2a-11dd-92ac-295bdf97101f/asa110151995en.html |archivedate=2014-07-07 }}</ref><ref name="International Committee of the Red Cross">{{cite web|year=1995|url=http://www.icrc.org/eng/resources/documents/misc/57jly2.htm|title=Afghanistan: escalation of indiscriminate shelling in Kabul|publisher=International Committee of the Red Cross|accessdate=2018-01-31|archive-date=2011-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110510012006/http://www.icrc.org/eng/resources/documents/misc/57jly2.htm|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 使得城市短暂恢复法律和秩序。法院再次开始运作，对政府军内部犯罪的个人进行定罪。<ref>{{youtube|id=Jnia-TUuCDs|title=BBC Newsnight 1995}}</ref>

1996年9月26日，[[塔利班|塔利班]]准备大举进攻，政府军事领导人[[艾哈迈德·沙阿·马苏德|艾哈迈德·沙阿·马苏德]]下令从喀布尔全面撤退，并向北逃去。第二天，塔利班占领喀布尔，建立了[[阿富汗伊斯兰酋长国|阿富汗伊斯兰酋长国]]。他们实行严格的[[伊斯兰教法|伊斯兰教法]]，限制妇女参加工作和接受教育<ref name="Physicians for Human Rights">{{cite web |year=1998 |url=http://physiciansforhumanrights.org/library/documents/reports/talibans-war-on-women.pdf |title=The Taliban's War on Women. A Health and Human Rights Crisis in Afghanistan |publisher=[[Physicians_for_Human_Rights|Physicians for Human Rights]] |access-date=2018-01-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070702234326/http://physiciansforhumanrights.org/library/documents/reports/talibans-war-on-women.pdf |archive-date=2007-07-02 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> ，砍断普通小偷的手脚，而臭名昭著的“促进善恶事业部”的打手小组负责监视公开殴打人民。<ref name="Physicians for Human Rights"/> 在强硬的塔利班政权期间，喀布尔是一个被遗弃的城市，许多居民长期离开，大多数基础设施遭到破坏，几乎没有任何教育或公共服务。

===21世纪===
[[File:Local_soldier_mentors_Afghan_police_in_Kabul.jpg|thumb]]
2001年11月，塔利班在美国入侵之后撤出喀布尔，随后[[北方联盟_(阿富汗)|北方联盟]]便占领了这座城市。 一个月后，由[[哈米德·卡尔扎伊|哈米德·卡尔扎伊]]总统领导的新政府开始运作。 与此同时，[[北约|北约]]领导的[[驻阿富汗国际维和部队|驻阿富汗国际维和部队]]（ISAF）开始部署在阿富汗。 许多外籍阿富汗人回国后，这座饱受战争蹂躏的城市开始了一些积极的发展。 全市人口从2001年的50万左右增加到近年来的300多万。 许多外国使馆也重新开放，城市从此一直在复苏。

截至2014年，阿富汗国家安全部队（ANSF）负责城市内外的安全工作。 喀布尔经常受到来自[[塔利班|塔利班]]、[[哈卡尼网络|哈卡尼网络]]，[[伊斯兰国|伊斯兰国]]和其他反国家集团进行的致命爆炸事件攻击。<ref name=US-blames-Pakistan>{{cite news |url=https://news.yahoo.com/pakistan-isi-urged-attacks-u-targets-officials-002201562.html |title=U.S. blames Pakistan agency in Kabul attack |publisher=Reuters |date=2011-09-22 |accessdate=2011-09-22 |archive-date=2011-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110925075845/http://news.yahoo.com/pakistan-isi-urged-attacks-u-targets-officials-002201562.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/09/17/us-pakistan-usa-haqqani-idUSTRE78G1RM20110917 |title=U.S. links Pakistan to group it blames for Kabul attack |date=2011-09-17 |publisher=Reuters |accessdate=2011-09-21 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924155251/http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/09/17/us-pakistan-usa-haqqani-idUSTRE78G1RM20110917 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2011/09/18/clinton-presses-pakistan-to-help-fight-haqqani-insurgent-group/ |title=Clinton Presses Pakistan to Help Fight Haqqani Insurgent Group |publisher=Fox News |date=2011-09-18 |accessdate=2011-09-21 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924181106/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2011/09/18/clinton-presses-pakistan-to-help-fight-haqqani-insurgent-group/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.yahoo.com/pakistan-condemns-us-comments-spy-agency-044440789.html;_ylt=A2KJ3vVYX3xOdRkA9EZXNyoA?rnd=005681253004174930714413 |title=Pakistan condemns US comments about spy agency |agency=Associated Press |date=2011-09-23 |accessdate=2011-09-23 |archive-date=2013-07-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130727053454/http://news.yahoo.com/pakistan-condemns-us-comments-spy-agency-044440789.html%3B_ylt%3DA2KJ3vVYX3xOdRkA9EZXNyoA?rnd=005681253004174930714413 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 政府雇员，士兵和普通平民都成为袭击的目标。<ref name=latimes>{{cite news |url=http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/world/la-fg-afghanistan-bombings-20111207,0,4701392.story |title=Two Afghanistan bombings aimed at Shiites kill at least 59 people |publisher=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]] |date=2008-12-07 |accessdate=2011-12-09 |first1=Hashmat |last1=Baktash |first2=Alex |last2=Rodriguez |archive-date=2012-01-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120125021608/http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/world/la-fg-afghanistan-bombings-20111207,0,4701392.story |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="ALISSA J. RUBIN">{{cite news
